               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390408-name-1415" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18390408-name-1415" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390408-name-1415" type="surname" value="UPTON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390408-name-1415" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM UPTON</persName>
                  </hi>. I am in the employ of Mr. John Stewart, of Cheap-side. On the 12th of April I had a coat thrown across the block in the shop—I saw the prisoner, about eight o'clock in the evening, walk into the shop, take it off the block, and walk out immediately—he ran and I ran, and called "Stop thief"—I never lost sight of him—he was stopped in Honey-lane-market—he dropped the coat—it was taken up and given to me—this is it—I am sure the prisoner is the person who took it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> I was returning home that day, and seeing the coat, I thought I could make a trifle of it, to make up my things, which I had lost—I was half <hi rend="italic">groggy</hi> at the time.</p>
